Project Concept and Planning
The aim of this project was to design and develop an interactive website inspired by EPIC: The Musical, focusing on its characters, themes, and music. 
The site is composed of clearly structured pages with consistent navigation, responsive layout, and multiple interactive components. Accessibility and usability were considered throughout development to ensure the website can be used across devices and by users with different needs.
Features
The project includes the following features and components:
•	Responsive navigation bar using Bootstrap 5.3.x
•	Character carousel layout displaying multiple characters
•	Custom flip card components with CSS animations
•	JavaScript driven character selection and filtering
•	Dark/light mode toggle using JavaScript
•	Embedded Spotify album players using <iframe> elements
•	Custom CSS layered on top of Bootstrap for theming
•	GitHub Pages hosting for live deployment
 
Design Decisions
The development process began with planning the site layout and identifying where interactivity would add value. The same layout was chosen across pages to improve usability and navigation. Bootstrap was used to support a responsive design while still allowing custom styling through CSS.
JavaScript was used to for interactivity. Event listeners handle user actions like clicking buttons, selecting characters, changing display modes and updating content. DOM manipulation was used to show and hide elements, update inputs, and control visual components without page reloads.
Biome was used to identify improvements in both JavaScript style and HTML accessibility.

 
