Testing
Testing was carried out throughout development using both manual and automated tools.
Manual Testing
•	Navigation tested across desktop and mobile screen sizes
•	JavaScript interactions tested for expected behaviour
•	Forms tested with valid and invalid input
•	Interactive elements tested for responsiveness and usability
Accessibility Testing
•	Embedded iframes updated with descriptive title attributes
•	Button elements updated with explicit type="button"
•	Semantic HTML used to improve screen reader support
Lighthouse (Chrome DevTools)
•	Performance, accessibility and best practice audits were run
•	Identified contrast and semantic issues were resolved (where time allowed)
Biome Linting Tool
Biome was used via the terminal to check formatting, accessibility and code quality. This process identified HTML structure issues, accessibility improvements, and JavaScript style suggestions. Critical findings were addressed, optional (yellow) warnings were reviewed but not required to be fully resolved. (Going forward I will run Biome earlier in the process to see where I am not using the most efficient code)
 

